## Goal

Extend the AgentsHeader from a 2-tab (List, Topology) view switcher to a 4-tab switcher with visual grouping: primary group (List, Topology) separated from management group (Denied, Access) by a border divider. Add mobile-responsive Select dropdown.

## File: `apps/client/src/layers/features/top-nav/ui/AgentsHeader.tsx`

The current component has:

```typescript
type ViewMode = 'list' | 'topology';

const VIEW_TABS: { mode: ViewMode; label: string }[] = [
  { mode: 'list', label: 'Agents' },
  { mode: 'topology', label: 'Topology' },
];
```

### Changes Required

1. **Extend ViewMode type** to include all 4 views:

```typescript
type ViewMode = 'list' | 'topology' | 'denied' | 'access';
```

2. **Replace VIEW_TABS with grouped structure** using icons from lucide-react (`List`, `Globe`, `ShieldBan`, `Lock`):

```typescript
import { Plus, ScanSearch, List, Globe, ShieldBan, Lock } from 'lucide-react';

const PRIMARY_TABS: { mode: ViewMode; label: string; icon: LucideIcon }[] = [
  { mode: 'list', label: 'Agents', icon: List },
  { mode: 'topology', label: 'Topology', icon: Globe },
];

const MANAGEMENT_TABS: { mode: ViewMode; label: string; icon: LucideIcon }[] = [
  { mode: 'denied', label: 'Denied', icon: ShieldBan },
  { mode: 'access', label: 'Access', icon: Lock },
];
```

3. **Update the desktop tab bar** (replacing the current `VIEW_TABS.map` block inside `{!isMobile && (...)}`). The new structure has 2+2 visual grouping with a border separator:

```tsx
{!isMobile && (
  <div className="bg-muted flex items-center rounded-md p-0.5">
    {/* Primary group */}
    {PRIMARY_TABS.map(({ mode, label }) => (
      <button
        key={mode}
        type="button"
        onClick={() => handleViewChange(mode)}
        className={cn(
          'text-xs font-medium transition-colors',
          viewMode === mode
            ? 'bg-background text-foreground rounded-md px-3 py-1 shadow-sm'
            : 'text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground px-3 py-1'
        )}
      >
        {label}
      </button>
    ))}
    {/* Separator */}
    <div className="mx-1 h-4 border-l" />
    {/* Management group */}
    {MANAGEMENT_TABS.map(({ mode, label }) => (
      <button
        key={mode}
        type="button"
        onClick={() => handleViewChange(mode)}
        className={cn(
          'text-xs font-medium transition-colors',
          viewMode === mode
            ? 'bg-background text-foreground rounded-md px-3 py-1 shadow-sm'
            : 'text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground px-3 py-1'
        )}
      >
        {label}
      </button>
    ))}
  </div>
)}
```

4. **Add mobile Select dropdown** (below the `{!isMobile && ...}` block). Import `Select`, `SelectContent`, `SelectItem`, `SelectTrigger`, `SelectValue` from `@/layers/shared/ui`:

```tsx
{isMobile && (
  <Select
    value={viewMode}
    onValueChange={(v) => handleViewChange(v as ViewMode)}
  >
    <SelectTrigger className="w-[140px]">
      <SelectValue />
    </SelectTrigger>
    <SelectContent>
      {[...PRIMARY_TABS, ...MANAGEMENT_TABS].map(({ mode, label }) => (
        <SelectItem key={mode} value={mode}>
          {label}
        </SelectItem>
      ))}
    </SelectContent>
  </Select>
)}
```

5. **Update `handleViewChange`** to accept the wider `ViewMode` type (already works since it's typed as ViewMode and we're extending the type).

## Acceptance Criteria

- Desktop: 4 tabs visible with separator between Topology and Denied
- Active tab has `bg-background` styling, others have `text-muted-foreground`
- Mobile: Select dropdown with all 4 view options
- Tab click calls `navigate({ to: '/agents', search: { view: mode } })`
- Existing "New Agent" and "Search for Projects" buttons unchanged

## Goal

Extend AgentsPage from 2-view (list/topology) to 4-view rendering with an AgentHealthDetail split-pane in the topology view. The `agent` search param drives the detail panel state.

## File: `apps/client/src/layers/widgets/agents/ui/AgentsPage.tsx`

The current component renders list or topology in Mode B. It needs:

1. New imports for `DeniedView`, `AccessView`, `AgentHealthDetail`, `Drawer`/`DrawerContent`, `useIsMobile`
2. Read `agent` from search params
3. Extend Mode B to render 4 views
4. Wire AgentHealthDetail split-pane into topology view
5. Mode A only triggers for `list` and `topology` views

### Changes Required

**Add imports:**

```typescript
import { useSearch, useNavigate } from '@tanstack/react-router';
import { AnimatePresence, motion } from 'motion/react';
import { DeniedView, AccessView } from '@/layers/features/agents-list';
import { AgentHealthDetail } from '@/layers/features/mesh';
import { Drawer, DrawerContent } from '@/layers/shared/ui';
import { useIsMobile, useOpenAgentDialog } from '@/layers/shared/model';
import { useDirectoryState } from '@/layers/entities/session';
```

**Read agent param and add navigation:**

```typescript
