Remove the `mesh` line and its comment. Note: `agent` stays because the Agent dialog (per-agent settings) is separate from the MeshPanel and is not being removed.

```typescript
export const dialogSearchSchema = z.object({
  // Settings
  settings: z.string().optional(),
  settingsSection: z.string().optional(),
  // Agent dialog
  agent: z.string().optional(),
  agentPath: z.string().optional(),
  // Other dialogs (parameterless — no tabs)
  tasks: z.string().optional(),
  relay: z.string().optional(),
});
```

IMPORTANT: The `agent` param in `dialogSearchSchema` is for the Agent settings dialog (`?agent=open&agentPath=/path`). It is separate from the new `agent` param in `agentsSearchSchema` (which is for the topology detail panel, `?agent=<id>`). They coexist because `mergeDialogSearch` merges the dialog schema into every route schema. On the `/agents` route, the Zod `.merge()` behavior means the route-specific `agent` (from `agentsSearchSchema`) takes precedence.

